b|url=https://www.unicef.org/myanmar/press-releases/international-legal-foundation-and-unicef-myanmar-join-forces-protect-children|title=The International Legal Foundation and UNICEF Myanmar join forces to protect children in conflict with the law|website=www.unicef.org}}</ref>\n\nThe ILF began work in Nepal in 2008, where it has worked on an estimated 7,500 cases across five districts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theilf.org/nepal|title=Nepal|website=The ILF}}</ref> In 2017, the Nepal program became locally-led, and was independently registered as the Public Defender Society of Nepal (PDS-Nepal).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pdsnepal.org/content/who-we-are|title=Public Defender Society: Mission and Story|website=pdsnepal.org}}</ref>\n\nThe ILF began work in the West Bank in 2010, opening its first office in [[Ramallah]].<ref name=\"International Legal Foundation, West Bank\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theilf.org/west-bank|title=West Bank|website=The ILF}}</ref> According to its website, staff have worked on more than 4,000 cases across 11 governorates.<ref name=\"International Legal Foundation, West Bank\" />\n\nThe ILF began its program in Tunisia in 2015.<ref name=\"International Legal Foundation, Tunisia\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theilf.org/tunisia|title=Tunisia|website=The ILF}}</ref> In 2020, the [[Tunis]] office took on its 500th case.<ref name=\"International Legal Foundation, Tunisia\" />\n\n=== United Nations ===\nThe ILF works alongside [[List of specialized agencies of the United Nations|United Nations agencies]] in a number of ways. The ILF actively participates in the [[United Nations Congress on Crime Prevention and Criminal Justice|UN Commission on Crime Prevention and Criminal Justice]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unodc.org/documents/commissions/CCPCJ/19-02848_CCPCJ_2019_Programme_ebook_NEW.pdf|title=UNITED NATIONS COMMISSION ON CRIME PREVENTION AND CRIMINAL JUSTICE, 28th Session. \"CCPCJ 2019 Programme\". Page 10.}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unodc.org/documents/commissions/CCPCJ/19-02848_CCPCJ_2019_Programme_ebook_NEW.pdf|title=UNITED NATIONS COMMISSION ON CRIME PREVENTION AND CRIMINAL JUSTICE, Twenty-fifth Session. \"CCPCJ Programme 2016\". Page 4.}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unodc.org/documents/commissions/CCPCJ/19-02848_CCPCJ_2019_Programme_ebook_NEW.pdf|title=UNITED NATIONS COMMISSION ON CRIME PREVENTION AND CRIMINAL JUSTICE, TWENTY-SECOND SESSION. \"Side_Events_Programme_22_CCPCJ_2013\". Page 4.}}</ref>, and retains consultative status with the [[United Nations Economic and Social Council]] (ECOSOC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esango.un.org/civilsociety/consultativeStatusSummary.do?profileCode=615040|title=United Nations Civil Society Participation (iCSO) \u2013 Login|website=esango.un.org}}</ref>\n\n=== International Legal Aid Conference ===\nIn 2014, the ILF co-founded the biennial International Conference on Access to Legal Aid in Criminal Justice Systems (ILAC) with the Open Society Justice Initiative (OSJI), the [[United Nations Development Programme]] (UNDP), and the [[United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime]] (UNODC).<ref name=\"About the ILAC\">{{Cite web|url=http://ilac2018.ge/|title=ILAC - Homepage|website=ilac2018.ge}}</ref> The conference highlights \u201cglobal efforts to implement the United Nations Principles and Guidelines on Access to Legal Aid in Criminal Justice Systems, which provide that States should put in place a comprehensive legal aid system.\u201d <ref name=\"About the ILAC\" />\nILAC has been held in the following locations: [[Johannesburg]], South Africa (2014),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unodc.org/pdf/criminal_justice/2014_Johannesburg_Declaration_on_Implementation_of_UNPGLA.pdf|title=The Johannesburg Declaration on the Implementation of the United Nations Principles and Guidelines on Access to Legal Aid in Criminal Justice Systems}}</ref> [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina  (2016),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unodc.org/documents/justice-and-prison-reform/LegalAid/E_CN15_2017_CRP2_e_V1703525.pdf|title=Outcome of the Second International Conference on Access to Legal Aid in Criminal Justice Systems, held in Buenos Aires, Argentina, 15-17 November 2016}}</ref> and [[Tbilisi]], Georgia (2018).<ref name=\"About the ILAC\" /> The 4th ILAC is scheduled to be held in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil in September 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ilac2020.rj.def.br/|title=ILAC 2020 - 4\u00ba International Conference on Access to Legal Aid Criminal Justice Systems|website=ilac2020.rj.def.br}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.theilf.org International Legal Foundation Official Website]\n\n[[Category:International nongovernmental organizations]]\n__INDEX__\n", "name_user": "LBuehner", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Legal_Foundation"}
